de.timmyrs.suprdiscordbot.structures

Class Embed

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.timmyrs.suprdiscordbot.structures.Structure
      • de.timmyrs.suprdiscordbot.structures.Embed

  • public class Embed
extends Structure
    Embed Structure. You can get an empty embed structure using DiscordAPI.createEmbed(). You can send an embed using Channel.sendMessage(Embed) and Channel.sendMessage(String, Embed).

    channel.sendMessage(discord.createEmbed()
        .setTitle("Example Embed")
        .setColor(0xF57C00)
        .setDescription("Hello, world!"));

    Author:
    timmyRS

      • addField

        public Embed addField(java.lang.String name,
                      java.lang.String value,
                      boolean inline)
        Adds an EmbedField object to fields You can have up to 25 fields. Inline fields may not display if the thumbnail and/or image is too big.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the field. Up to 256 chars.
        value - Value of the field. Up to 2048 chars.
        inline - Whether or not this field should display inline (true = to the right of the last field, false = below the last field).
        Returns:
        this
        See Also:
        EmbedField
